SAFA president Danny Jordaan has landed himself a seat at the table of the Confederation of African Football (Caf) at the governing body's executive committee meeting in Cairo. Jordaan has been named Caf's third vice-president behind chiefs Ahmad Ahmad, first VP Omari Constant of Congo and second VP Fouzi Lekjaa of Morocco. The election was held after a new executive committee was voted into power, ahead of the closing ceremony and final of the 2019 Africa Cup of Nations taking place on Friday evening.   